Netflix will discuss Q1 2011 earnings after market close.
The key trend to watch will be the potential for sustained subscriber growth momentum.

Netflix launched a discounted streaming-only plan that has spurred subscriptions, but headwinds like Amazon's Prime video streaming service and Netflix's substantial subscriber base (already approaching that of Comcast ( CMCSA )) could decelerate growth.

See our complete analysis of Netflix stock here

P&G embarked on a goal to acquire a billion additional consumers by 2014/15, which naturally put its focus on the world's two most populous nations - China and India.

To cater to these high-growth but low-income level consumer markets, P&G has had to launch low-priced and smaller-sized variants of its products, expand its distribution network and enter more product categories in these countries.
